----------------------------------------
Proteomaps workflow and data directories
----------------------------------------

CODE
  python - python code
  matlab - matlab code

DATA RESOURCES (functional hierarchy)
  genomic_data

PROTEOME DATA (different stages of processing)
  data_sets         - directories for data 
  data_paver_input  - input data for paver
  data_paver_output - output data from paver (images and html)
  html              - processed html (to be copied into website directory)


To create a new set ("bundle") of data sets to be analysed together:

 o create a new directory for the data bundle 
 o create the file filenames.csv with all necessary information
 o create a new directory for the paver input files (../data_paver_input/data_for_paver_[data bundle])
 o create a shell script CreateProteomaps.sh calling CreateProteomaps.py
 o run the shell script

Afterwards:

 o use the files from (in ../data_paver_input/data_for_paver_[data bundle]) and run paver
 o save the output files in (in ../data_paver_output/proteomaps_[data bundle])
 o use Make_proteomaps_html.py to create html files
 o Possibly, use copy_files_to_website.py to put the maps on the website